    "demographics": "The Netherlands has 17.8 million people, making it one of Europe's most densely populated and urbanized nations. Amsterdam is a global financial and technology hub. The economy is driven by trade, agriculture, technology, and financial services. The Randstad region (Amsterdam-Rotterdam-Utrecht-The Hague) is the economic heart. The population is highly educated, multilingual, and digitally sophisticated. High immigration, particularly tech talent, maintains a dynamic workforce.",
