    "demographics": "Saudi Arabia has 36 million people with one of the youngest populations in the Gulf — roughly 70% under age 35. This creates enormous demand for mobile-first banking. The economy is undergoing the most ambitious transformation program in the region through Vision 2030, diversifying from oil into tourism (NEOM, Red Sea), entertainment, sports, technology, and financial services. Women's workforce participation is increasing rapidly, creating new banking segments. The expatriate population of approximately 13 million requires diverse financial services.",
    "banking_sector": "Saudi Arabia's banking sector is large and increasingly dynamic. Saudi National Bank (SNB) became the largest after the 2021 merger of NCB and Samba Financial Group. Al Rajhi Bank is the world's largest Islamic bank by market cap and has been a digital transformation leader. Riyad Bank, Banque Saudi Fransi, Saudi British Bank (SABB), and Arab National Bank round out the major players. SAMA (Saudi Central Bank) has licensed three digital banks: STC Bank (backed by telecom giant STC), D360 Bank, and Saudi Digital Bank — signaling a clear regulatory push toward digital innovation.",
    "digital_banking": "Saudi Arabia has leapfrogged in digital banking adoption. SAMA's ambitious agenda includes open banking regulations (launched 2022-23), the Fawri+ instant payment system, and digital banking licensing. Al Rajhi Bank's mobile app is one of the most downloaded banking apps in the Middle East. STC Bank launched with a purely digital model targeting the young population. The government's push for cashless transactions (targeting 70% by 2025) is driving rapid adoption. SADAD serves as the national electronic bill payment system.",
    "consumer_segments": "Saudi retail consumers are young, mobile-first, and increasingly demanding. The growing female workforce creates new banking needs. SMEs are a government priority — MONSHA'AT (the SME authority) is driving programs to increase SME contribution to GDP from 20% to 35%. Corporate banking is massive, serving Vision 2030 mega-projects. Islamic banking dominates, requiring Sharia-compliant product structures across all segments. Wealth management is growing rapidly with increasing private wealth among Saudi families and a growing affluent middle class.",
    "spending_trends": "Consumer spending is growing as entertainment, dining, and lifestyle options expand under Vision 2030. E-commerce is booming. Government is promoting home ownership through mortgage programs, creating a growing housing finance market. Investment in local equity markets is increasing through Tadawul. Young Saudis are heavy users of BNPL services and digital wallets.",
